Articles.Content: Memory crash. You have graphics mods and some pretty large part packs, try removing some mods or check out this thread. https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/120387-some-relief-for-memory-outage-crashes/

You have lots of memory available so that leads me to think of two possibilities ....

I notice that you are running in steam ... It could very well be that you are running KSP in 32 bit as that is the default steam setting ... Read the following linked post for help on changing the default to 64 bit

If the above doesn't fix your problem then it is likely that you have a mod that is not playing nice with others ... Read the following so you can help us help you
